My vimrc uses Vundle plugin management system to have a well organized vim
directory. Vundle also ensures that the latest versions of your plugins are
installed and makes it easy to keep them up to date.


Plugins (By alphabetical order)
================================

Name                   Description
-------                ------------
neocomplcache          amazing autocomplete plugin
nerdcommenter          wrangle code comments, regardless of filetype
nerdtree               file explorer
python-mode            python support using pylint, rope, pyflakes, etc
tagbar                 provides a panel to easily navigate via files tags
undotree               keeps undid changes
vim-autoclose          automatically close brackets, parens, quotes, etc
vim-nerdtree-tabs      makes nerdtree independent of tabs
